The 1934 season of the &lt;a href="Mitropa%20Cup"&gt;Mitropa Cup&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; club tournament was won by &lt;a href="Bologna%20F.C.%201909"&gt;AGC Bologna&lt;/a&gt; who defeated &lt;a href="FC%20Admira%20Wacker%20M%C3%B6dling"&gt;Admira Wien&lt;/a&gt; 7–4 on aggregate in the final. It was Bologna's second victory in the competition, having won it previously in 1932. The two legs of the final were played on 5 September and 9 September.
This was the eighth edition of the tournament. Holders &lt;a href="FK%20Austria%20Wien"&gt;FK Austria Wien&lt;/a&gt; were eliminated in the first round
Finals.
